{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"assign"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:d","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"double"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"tileLodZoomShift"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Shift applied to the Zoom level during LOD calculation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A negative value shifts the Zoom level to a coarser level reducing quality but improving","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"performance A positive value shifts the Zoom level to a finer level increasing details but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"negatively affecting performance A value of zero (default) does not apply any shift to the Zoom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level It is not recommended to change the default value unless performance is critical and the loss","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of quality is acceptable. A value of -1 reduces the number of displayed tiles by a factor of 4 on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"average It is recommended to first configure the pixelRatio before adjusting TileLodZoomShift.","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Camera based tile level of detail controls"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/tileLodZoomShift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0